description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a rewarding job with great pay and benefits?, Do you want to join a company that cares?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Alpha Health Care - The Lakes Care Home in Great Wyrley are specialists in Dementia Care and are currently recruiting for dedicated and caring team players to join us as Healthcare Assistants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As Healthcare Assistants, it is desirable that you have experience of a similar role in Elderly Care. It is equally important that you can demonstrate the right behaviours and attitude for working in an Adult Care environment. A full induction programme will be provided, alongside formal training opportunities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The benefits of this Healthcare Assistant position include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- £9.00 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Paid breaks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Night shifts available - 8pm - 8am&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Company pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Dedicated In-house training team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free parking on site&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Easily commutable from Bloxwich, Walsall, Wolverhampton, Great Wyrley, Cannock, Hednesford and surrounding areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Uniform provided&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- 5.6 weeks holiday entitlement per year&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Alpha Health Care, we are committed to keeping our staff safe from the risk presented by Coronavirus (COVID-19). We have introduced a number of steps to increase protection for our staff which include increased access to hand washing and hand sanitising facilities, testing protocols, full access to PPE and welfare support for all our staff.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
